## 💎 The 10 Beauties of LiveCold

### Beauty 1: SOP as Single Source of Truth

Most cold chain systems have hardcoded temperature thresholds scattered across 10 files. **We don't.**

Our SOP document ([cold_chain_SOP.txt](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/watched_docs/cold_chain_SOP.txt)) contains a machine-readable block:
```
<!-- PRODUCT_TEMP_RANGES
Vaccines:2:8
Frozen_Meat:-18:-12
Dairy:2:6
Seafood:-1:2
...
-->
```

[sop_parser.py](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/sop_parser.py) reads this at startup. Every component — simulators, risk model, shipment factory — calls [get_product_temp_ranges()](file:///Users/tarunsingh/Desktop/hackathon/hack/sop_parser.py#104-125) to get the ranges. **Change one file → the entire system adapts.**

> **PPT Slide**: *"One document. One truth. Zero config drift."*

---

### Beauty 2: 4-Layer Anomaly Detection

A sensor glitch at -999°C shouldn't trigger a ₹25 Lakh diversion. Our anomaly detector has **4 defense layers**:

| Layer | What It Catches | Example | Action |
|-------|----------------|---------|--------|
| **L1: Physical Bounds** | Impossible temperatures | Dairy sensor reads 500°C | ❌ Discard entirely |
| **L2: Rate-of-Change** | Sensor faults (sudden jumps) | Temp jumps 20°C in 2 seconds | 🔄 Use last good reading |
| **L3: Z-Score Statistical** | Outliers from rolling mean | Reading 3.5σ from 20-sample mean | 🔄 Use rolling mean |
| **L4: Stuck Sensor** | Frozen/dead sensors | 10 identical readings in a row | ⚠️ Flag for maintenance |

**Why it matters:** Without this, ~9% of readings would trigger false alerts. Our pipeline rejects bad data BEFORE it enters the risk model.

> **PPT Slide**: *"4 layers of defense. Zero false diversions."*

---

### Beauty 3: Sigmoid Risk Model + Cost Optimizer

We don't use simple IF-ELSE rules. Our risk model uses a **sigmoid function** for smooth probability curves:

```
risk = sigmoid(deviation × 1.8 + exposure × 0.2) × ETA_factor
```

Then the **Diversion Optimizer** makes economically rational decisions:

```
Expected Loss (Continue) = Risk × Cargo Value
Total Divert Cost = Fuel Cost + Residual Risk × Cargo Value

If Continue Loss > Divert Cost → DIVERT
```

**Supports 3 routing modes:**
- 🛡️ **SAFETY** — nearest hub always (for vaccines, pharma)
- ⚖️ **BALANCED** — optimize cost vs. safety (dairy, seafood)
- 🌿 **ECO** — minimize CO₂, accept longer detours (fruits, flowers)

> **PPT Slide**: *"Not rule-based. Math-based. Every decision has a number behind it."*

---

### Beauty 4: Intelligent Hub Manager

15 real cold storage hubs across India. Finding the right one isn't just "find the nearest" — it's a **5-filter intelligent match**:

1. ✅ Hub must be **available** (not in maintenance)
2. 🌡️ Hub must have the **correct temperature zone** (Ultra-Cold for vaccines, Frozen for ice cream, Chilled for dairy)
3. 📦 Hub must have **enough capacity** (available tonnes > cargo weight)
4. 🚗 **Traffic-aware ETA** — not just distance, but actual travel time considering:
   - Time-of-day traffic multipliers (e.g., 1.9× at 6 PM in Mumbai)
   - City congestion zones (Delhi NCR 1.8×, Mumbai Metro 1.7×)
   - Two-phase calculation: departure traffic + arrival-hour traffic
5. 🔧 **Repair station filter** — for anomaly alerts, find hubs with repair capability

Sorted by ETA (not distance!) — because 50 km in Delhi traffic takes longer than 100 km on a highway.

> **PPT Slide**: *"Not nearest by distance. Nearest by actual arrival time."*

---

### Beauty 5: Real-Time Pathway RAG Pipeline

We use **Pathway** — a real-time data processing framework — for live SOP Q&A:

- `pw.io.fs.read(mode="streaming")` watches the SOP file
- When you edit the SOP, Pathway's dataflow detects the change
- The next query automatically uses the **updated content**
- REST API at `/v2/answer` accepts natural language questions
- LLM generates SOP-cited action checklists

**The demo flow:**
1. Open SOP Editor → change Dairy range from `2:6` to `2:10`
2. Ask: "What is the safe range for dairy?"
3. Answer instantly reflects the new range
4. Revert → answer updates again

> **PPT Slide**: *"Edit the SOP. The AI learns it in 2 seconds. Not 2 days."*

---

### Beauty 6: Three Notification Conditions

Not just "send an alert." Three distinct, intelligent notification triggers:

| Condition | Trigger | Who Gets Notified | Content |
|-----------|---------|-------------------|---------|
| **DIVERT** | Risk > 60% + cost-optimal | 📲 Driver via WhatsApp | Hub name, Google Maps link, ETA, contact number |
| **Repair Alert** | 3+ anomalies in 10 min from same truck | 📲 Driver + Ops Team | Nearest repair station with ETA |
| **Delivery Complete** | Manual trigger or shipment arrival | 📧 Client via Email | Full compliance report with carbon credits |

**Deduplication built-in**: DIVERT notifications have a 5-minute cooldown per shipment. Repair alerts only fire once per truck until reset.

> **PPT Slide**: *"The right message. To the right person. At the right time."*

---

### Beauty 7: Live GPS Re-Routing

When a DIVERT decision is made, the truck doesn't just get a notification — **it physically changes course**:

1. Pipeline publishes diversion order to `livecold/divert` with hub coordinates
2. GPS simulator subscribes to this topic
3. Truck's `target_lat/lon` changes from original destination to hub
4. On the dashboard map, you can **watch the truck turn** toward the hub
5. When truck arrives (within ~1 km), it resets and continues original route

> **PPT Slide**: *"Not just alerts. Actual re-routing in real-time."*

---

### Beauty 8: Carbon Credits & Sustainability Engine

Every diversion prevents food waste. We calculate the **net CO₂ benefit**:

```
CO₂ Saved = (Production Emissions of Wasted Food) - (Extra Fuel Emissions of Detour)
Carbon Credits = CO₂ Saved × ₹1,000/tonne
```

Using real industry data:
- Dairy waste: 8.5 kg CO₂e per kg
- Meat waste: 27.0 kg CO₂e per kg
- Seafood waste: 5.1 kg CO₂e per kg

The Analytics page shows total CO₂ avoided, credits earned in ₹, and breakdown by product type.

> **PPT Slide**: *"Save the cargo. Save the planet. Earn carbon credits."*

---

### Beauty 9: Per-Shipment Routing Mode with Bidirectional Sync

Each shipment gets a default routing mode based on its product type. But the operations manager can **override it mid-journey**:

1. **Dashboard → Pipeline**: Manager changes SHP_14 (Fruits) from ECO → SAFETY
2. Dashboard publishes to `livecold/routing-mode` via MQTT
3. Pipeline receives it, updates `objective_mode` for that shipment
4. Next decision uses SAFETY rules (nearest hub, ignore CO₂ cost)
5. Pipeline decisions reflect the new mode back to dashboard
6. Override is protected — pipeline can't revert a manual change

> **PPT Slide**: *"Automatic defaults. Manual overrides. Always in sync."*

---

### Beauty 10: Driver Dashboard with Notification Inbox

Not just an ops dashboard — we built a **mobile-friendly driver view**:

- `/driver/SHP_1` shows everything the driver needs:
  - Current temperature with color-coded status
  - Risk level gauge
  - Route information (origin → destination)
  - **Notification inbox** — all WhatsApp/email notifications sent to this driver
  - Routing mode display (updates in real-time when ops changes it)

Notifications are pushed from the main dashboard via:
1. Ops clicks "Send" on an alert
2. API pushes notification to driver inbox
3. MQTT delivers it to the driver dashboard in real-time

> **PPT Slide**: *"Ops sees the big picture. Driver sees their truck. Both in real-time."*

