## 🔢 Technical Highlights for Judges

### Architecture Decisions Worth Highlighting

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| **MQTT as message bus** | Decouples simulators ↔ pipeline ↔ dashboard. Any component can restart independently. |
| **Pipeline as single brain** | All risk calculations happen in ONE place. Dashboard only DISPLAYS decisions. No duplicate logic. |
| **SSE (Server-Sent Events)** | Real-time dashboard updates without WebSocket complexity. One-directional, lightweight. |
| **Thread-safe global state** | `threading.Lock()` on hub state, anomaly tracker, notification store. No race conditions. |
| **LLM fallback chain** | Tries Pathway RAG → rotates 5 Gemini models → rotates 2 API keys → cooldown on rate limits. Never fails silently. |
| **Singleton pattern** | `anomaly_detector`, `alert_notifier` are global singletons shared across threads. |
| **SOP file watcher** | Polls every 2 seconds, detects mtime change, reloads SOP, clears RAG cache, pushes SSE. |
| **Diversion dedup** | Pipeline level (`already_diverted` set) + Dashboard level (`diverted_shipments_saved` dict). |

### Scale Numbers

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Active shipments | 25 concurrent |
| Sensor readings/second | ~50 (25 trucks × 2 sensors/sec) |
| Hub database | 15 hubs across 15 Indian cities |
| City congestion zones | 8 major metros modeled |
| Product types | 9 (Vaccines, Meat, Dairy, Seafood, Vegetables, Fruits, Pharma, Ice Cream, Flowers) |
| Temperature zones | 6 (Ultra-Cold, Deep Frozen, Frozen, Chilled, Cool, Ambient) |
| API endpoints | 20+ REST endpoints |
| Notification types | 3 (WhatsApp DIVERT, WhatsApp Repair, Email Delivery) |

