## 🔑 Questions Judges Might Ask (With Answers)

**Q: How is this different from existing cold chain solutions?**
> Existing solutions alert AFTER the damage. We predict, decide, and re-route in real-time. Our sigmoid risk model provides probability-based decisions, not binary alerts.

**Q: How do you handle sensor faults?**
> 4-layer anomaly detection: physical bounds, rate-of-change, z-score statistical, stuck sensor. ~9% of readings are filtered. Zero false diversions.

**Q: How do you decide which hub to divert to?**
> 5-filter intelligent match: availability, temperature zone compatibility, capacity, traffic-aware ETA (with congestion zones), and optionally repair station capability. Sorted by actual arrival time, not distance.

**Q: What about the CO₂ impact of diversions?**
> We calculate net CO₂: waste-prevented emissions minus extra fuel emissions. In ECO mode, diversions are avoided if CO₂ penalty exceeds the threshold — unless cargo loss would be catastrophic.

**Q: Can the operator override the AI?**
> Yes. Routing mode can be changed per-shipment mid-journey. The change syncs bidirectionally between dashboard and pipeline via MQTT. Manual overrides are protected from being reverted.

**Q: What happens when the SOP changes?**
> Our file watcher detects the change in 2 seconds, reloads the SOP, clears the RAG cache. The next query uses updated content. We also have a Pathway pipeline (`pw.io.fs.read(streaming)`) for real-time document processing.

**Q: Is this production-ready?**
> Docker + docker-compose for deployment. Health check endpoint. API key rotation with rate-limit handling. Thread-safe state management. AWS deployment guide included.
